      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA02d094n2-ptr" id="PJA02d094n2">2</a>
       
   <p>William, Lord Russell and Algernon Sidney, members of the Council of Six, were both executed for the Councils part in the conspiracies of 1683; John, Lord Somers sponsored in Parliament the Bill of Rights and other important measures; and Benjamin Hoadly, prominent whig bishop, was author of <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">The Original and Institution of Civil Government Discussd</span>, London, 1710 (Caroline Robbins, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">The Eighteenth-Century Commonwealthman</span>, Cambridge, 1959, p. 29, 7881, 84, 408).</p>

